(a) regulations under section 37;
(b) regulations under section 39;
(c) regulations under section 150, unless they are regulations under that section that only make provision that corresponds or is similar to provision made or capable of being made by a statutory instrument that is itself subject to annulment in pursuance of a resolution of either House of Parliament;
(d) regulations under section 172;
(e) regulations under section 187;
(f) regulations made by the Secretary of State under section 189(1);
(g) regulations under section 190(5) or (6);
(h) regulations under section 203 that amend or repeal provision made by an Act.
